phrases: There are likely no Titans among the 104th Cadet Corps recruits!
The 104th Cadet Corps were kept isolated under suspicion of Titans within their ranks.
But with the sudden appearance of Titans, couriers were dispatched to warn each district.
today marks the new darkest day in humanity's history!
If ever humankind needed to give its all, that time is now!
The because of this crisis remains in the dark.
For now, no one yet knows.
I must say, what a clever idea.
What the hell does all this mean?
Would Titans break walls with Titans in them?
They busted the wall into our city.
There is no crevices between the rocks or any signs of cracking.
We cannot really tell how they are made.
So what if they are made of hardened Titan skin?
It must be pretty versatile if Annie can encase herself.
We are supposed to leave in 5 minutes!
There is something I need to confirm-
He is been ready for a while now.
Took longer to prepare than we thought.

Nick and I are best buddies.
Do not let him bother you.

Erwin picked them out for a reason.

But everything up until Ehrmich is safe.
We will save time going through there.
This whole time, Titans have been protecting us from Titans.
There is Titans inside the walls and he is known about it?!
But now he is coming with us to witness the harsh reality.
Will his beliefs be strong enough for him to stay silent?
Or will seeing it with his own eyes make him question himself?
If there is something you know, tell us about it!
Nothing's more important than keeping humans from going extinct!
You are still not fully healed.
There is more than one way to get answers.
I may be injured and useless right now, but it does not take much to watch one man.

What if the reason he does not talk
is because he knows something more important than the fate of humanity?
My village is deep in the forest!
Get it out of yer mouth!
We fixin' to smoke that for winter, ya moron!
Have you asked yerself why the world is a-changing?
Why these past few years the forest be shrinkin' and game harder to find?
Have you ever thunk about it?
It is'because more people be comin' and taking food and game from the forest.
That is why I am hungry.
They lost their homes and got no place to go.
They knocked a hole straight through Wall Maria.
You can feed a hell of a lot more people by clearin' the forest and plantin' grain.
Maybe it is time for our family to let go of the forest and give up huntin' for good.
The government said they would pay us.
Every horse that we raise is money in our pockets.
If we give up huntin', we be givin' up who we are!
Why should we give a hoot about the people who make fun of our lifestyle?
It is because... we are all part of the same world.
We have always been pack animals.
Sure, we all live our different ways.
But when space is this short, we got to join the group and do what is best to-
We have lived here all our lives, just like the way our ancestors taught us!
We do not owe nothing to any outsiders!
Ya can live here in this forest, along with the others who think the same.
Are ya willin' to die for that choice?
No matter what trouble comes yer way, ya cannot go beggin' for help.
If you are not there for them, do not expect them to be there for you.
I am willin' to give up our traditions if it means I can live with my family.
Goes to show ya our world's connected, whether you like it or not.
Are you that much of a scaredy-cat?
Is it that hard for you to leave this forest behind and get along with others?
It is been 3 years since I have been back.
Surely he realized something was amiss and fled...
They have already come this far?!
This place is not safe for people anymore.
In addition to the cities at the walls, there exist villages of various sizes contained within the walls.
They exist to provide goods and food to the people in the cities, though containing a higher population overall.
Information Available for Public Disclosure Scattered Villages
If I do not slice it off, it will just heal back up!
There is no need to worry.
Why are you so nice when you talk?

But not a single person came to help.
All I could do was watch.
You are really starting to tick me off.
That stupid way you talk politely to everyone.
Why do not you talk to other cadets like normal?
You are embarrassed by the way people sound from your village.
I am surprised an idiot like you cares so much.
You cannot do anything but hunt, and you are afraid of people, to top it off.
I bet you do not have a single good reason for aiming to become a soldier.
You going to care what other people think and be someone you are not your whole life?
You are fine as is, so talk in your own words for crying out loud.
There is nothing wrong with the way she talks!
Sasha is who Sasha wants to be.
Her words will always be her own.
And I happen to like her.
Still, even if she changed the way she talks,
it will not change the fact that she is annoying.
You know, not everyone is as insensitive as you.
Why do I remember, now of all times...
Run as far as you can.
I promise someone will be there to help you.
You might not find them right away...
But still, keep running until you do!
If I take out both eyes, it will buy us plenty of time.
All it is... is a big...
I slipped out thanks to that blood.
Now I have got to find that girl!
We been givin' horses to everyone in the area.

You fought off a Titan for that girl, did not ya?

I am sure my family is safe and sound.
Shaking off the dread of Titans appearing in his hometown,
Battle erupts across the land while the mystery of the Titans remains.
Eren and the others heading for Ehrmich District
receive a clue that might reveal the truth.
